Shorea robusta

   [9747.jpg]
    Authority   Gaertner f.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Malvales:Dipterocarpaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9747

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A tall deciduous tree, though seldom completely leafless, reaching a
   height of 35-45 m. The trunk is about 1/2 of the tree height and may
   reach a girth of 3 m. The crown is elongated in youth, later more
   rounded. On infertile site the tree may reach 20-25 m in height and
   1.5-2 m in girth.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Sal, Hal, Borsal, Shal, Sakhu, Sakhwa, Salwa, Sakwa, Soringhi, Gugal,
   Thamba, Sarjakamu
   FURTHER INF
   Sal is found both in undulating and flat country, but it thrives at
   lower slopes and in valleys. It can be found at altitudes between
   75-2000 m. Sal is one of the main commercial timbers of India.
   Yearly potential volume production may be 8-12 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Joshi H 1980 pp 8-321 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, PH, KTMP, FER, LIG, DRA, DEP,
   USE]
   Shrestha B 1989 pp 130
   Zabala N 1990 pp 79-83 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DEP, FER, TEXT, DRA, USE]

